  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nThe `/eth/v1/beacon/headers/{block_id}` endpoint does not support hex encoded block roots with 0x prefix:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"message\": \"Invalid block ID: could not parse block ID: strconv.ParseUint: parsing \\\"0x9dd67540a9c17a4ba2d8346b545ffb1f6d4c0412ffb6a5ab36634440314901dd\\\": invalid syntax\",\r\n  \"code\": 400\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAccording to the specs, this should be allowed: [Beacon/getBlockHeader](https://ethereum.github.io/beacon-APIs/#/Beacon/getBlockHeader).\r\n\r\n\r\nThe error is triggered here:\r\nhttps://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/develop/beacon-chain/rpc/lookup/blocker.go#L78\r\n\r\nI guess the logic in line 72-76 should handle blockroot arguments,  but it assumes a binary `id` instead of hex encoding  \n\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\n\n_No response_\n\n### ðŸ”¬ Minimal Reproduction\n\ncall `/eth/v1/beacon/headers/{block_id}` with any hex encoded block root as `block_id`\n\n### Error\n\n_No response_\n\n### Platform(s)\n\n_No response_\n\n### What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?\n\n_No response_",
